<div id="comment_64117717" class="cw">
	<div id="comment_top_64117717" class="commentTop newcomment">
		<div class="title">
			<h4><a id="comment_link_64117717" name="comment_link_64117717" href="//it.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=23176695&amp;cid=64117717" onclick="return D2.setFocusComment(64117717)" >Re:RTO is disproportionately a big company phenome</a>


		 	<span id="comment_score_64117717" class="score"> (<a href="#" onclick="getModalPrefs('modcommentlog', 'Moderation Comment Log', 64117717); return false"><span class=opt>Score:</span>4</a>, Insightful)</span></h4>
		</div>
		<div class="details">
			<span class="by"><span class="byby">by </span><a href="//slashdot.org/~jacks+smirking+reven">jacks smirking reven</a>  <span class="uid"><a href="//slashdot.org/~jacks+smirking+reven">( 909048 )</a></span></a></span><span class="writes" style="display:none"> writes:</span> 
			<span class="otherdetails" id="comment_otherdetails_64117717">		
		on Saturday December 30, 2023 @05:30PM (<span class="ind"></span><a href="//it.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=23176695&amp;cid=64117717">#64117717</a>)
		<small> </small>
</span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64117717"><p>This is also the result of decades of bad urban zoning with this idea of all highly corporate downtown areas flanked by suburbs and residentials rather than a more mixed approach, which ironically we already know is a much more favorable approach from, well, the largest cities.</p><p>Those cities also don't get to tap the extra revenue from the resident because the workers usually don't actually live in that particular city but a town outside it.  Combine that with the fact that most suburban districts lose money and end up subsidized by the city they surround and you've created a sort of urban death spiral.</p><p>This also exacerbated the problem in the first place since everyone has to commute into the area where people work as opposed to just leaving nearby it and tada, long commutes.</p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64117717">
